      "content": {
        "title": "Revision Shoulder Arthroplasty — Core Principles",
        "definition": "Reoperation for failed shoulder replacement due to infection, instability, loosening, or component malposition.",
        "summary": "Instability after anatomic TSA may require conversion to reverse. Periprosthetic infection follows similar principles to hip and knee."
      },
